## Cancel reward bonus

> Request example

```shell
curl 'https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/basic/cancel' \
    -X 'PATCH' \
    -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    --data-raw '{"identifier":"PHONE", "shop_id":"SHOP_ID", "shop_secret":"SHOP_SECRET", "id":"TRANSACTION_ID"}'
```

> The above command returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
    "status": "success"
}
```

Method cancels a reward bonus which was created by `loyalty/basic/event_bonus` method. This method can cancel only reward bonuses which have `cancellable` flag. List of all reward bonuses can be received from `loyalty/bonuses/event_bonus_history` method.

### HTTP Request

`PATCH https://<%= config[:api_endpoint] %>/loyalty/basic/cancel`

### Query Parameters

| Parameter   | Required | Description                                      |
|-------------|----------|--------------------------------------------------|
| shop_id     | true     | Your API key                                     |
| shop_secret | true     | Your API secret key                              |
| identifier  | true     | User's phone number (loyalty program identifier) |
| id          | true     | Transaction ID                                   |


### API response

| Name      | Type   | Description       |
|-----------|--------|-------------------|
| status    | String | Response status   |
